A vintage-style illustration depicting a dusty filing cabinet drawer pulled open, revealing manila folders with one folder dramatically dissolving into scattered paper fragments and ghost-like wisps, while an old brass compass nearby spins wildly with its needle pointing nowhere. The scene is bathed in warm sepia tones with soft vignette edges, featuring worn wooden desk surfaces and antique brass hardware. Floating translucent echoes of the dissolving folder linger in the air like afterimages, suggesting something removed but not truly gone. The composition evokes the feeling of a phantom reference, an invisible tether to something that no longer exists.
